CHANGELOG.md:67:- Added focused regression coverage for the operator-diagnostics sampler line (`OperatorDiagnostics.sample_source`) in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics_sample_status.py`, pinning the four discrete states the formatter must produce: sampling-only renders `currently sampling …` without a playback fragment, playing-only renders `playing sample …` without a sampling fragment, both-active joins the two phrases with ` · `, and the all-idle case degrades to `unavailable` so the daemon never serializes an empty sampler line.
CHANGELOG.md:71:- Wired active-song human phrase capture into the live listeners: new `senseweave.phrase_capture_runtime.ActiveSongPhraseCapture` gates `PhraseCaptureWriter` on fresh `/tmp/composer_state.json` song context, `midi_keyboard_listener.py` and `theramini_listener.py` now feed qualifying >5s phrases into `samples/keyboard/` and `samples/theramini/` with validated song/key/tempo sidecars, `PhraseCaptureWriter` now exposes `reset()` for safe song-boundary drops, and `human_phrase_capture_verify.py` plus new runtime/integration tests simulate both sources without hardware and validate the resulting paths and tags.
CHANGELOG.md:100:- Fixed the long-section tracker compile bug that was turning songs into isolated sustained tones: `tracker_compiler.py` now converts large section budgets into repeat counts plus modest note-length scaling, and `music_tracker.py` quantizes those repeats into real repeated phrase cycles instead of stretching a handful of notes across the whole scene.
CHANGELOG.md:101:- Finished the next score-tree composition pass: `tracker_compiler.py` now derives and enriches a fresh score per section, applies section-function and motif-aware phrase transforms before tracker quantization, and `music_tracker.py` now varies repeated cycles inside long sections, so longer pieces can develop through distinct section writing instead of only looping one shared phrase body.
CHANGELOG.md:102:- Added internal phrase-family development inside longer sections: `Phrase` now carries metadata, `tracker_compiler.py` expands section bodies into recursive families like `A`, `A_prime`, and `B`, and `music_tracker.py` annotates emitted steps with `internal_phrase_family` so development sections can be tested and diagnosed as more than literal loops.
CHANGELOG.md:103:- Coordinated those internal phrase families across tracker roles: shared root/function profiles now shape melody, bass, counter, and color variants together, and tracker steps expose `internal_family_root_degree` plus `internal_family_function` for diagnostics and future orchestration consumers.
CHANGELOG.md:107:- Added section-level motif development and local harmonic progressions: `tracker_compiler.py` now labels each section as statement, sequence/fragment, contrast inversion, recall answer, liquidation, or residue, reshapes phrase material accordingly, and applies section-local progressions that are exposed on tracker scenes and steps for bass/progression verification.
CHANGELOG.md:108:- Added section-level rhythmic development: `tracker_compiler.py` now maps section functions to named rhythm cells such as steady statement, syncopated fragment, half-time displacement, recall groove, and residue breath, reshaping phrase durations/accents and exposing `rhythm_development` / `rhythm_cell` through tracker metadata.
CHANGELOG.md:163:- Tightened title-hook coherence again: `hook_engine.py` now chooses title phrases from image-field-aware pools that also react to cadence, progression profile, hook type, and repertoire source titles, so CypherClaw can move between labels like `Low Light`, `Electric Circuits`, `Moving Lines`, and `Open Thresholds` without collapsing back to generic or repeated adjective-noun pairs.
CHANGELOG.md:165:- Tightened hook-language quality at the source: `hook_engine.py` now normalizes rough historical phrases like `carry the line wide` and `open the room open`, and `repertoire_memory.py` repairs those forms on load/store so they stop resurfacing through recall.
CHANGELOG.md:170:- Made repertoire answer hooks less literal and less repetitive: `hook_engine.py` now chooses among contextual phrase-level answer variants based on family/cadence/song state, so recalled hook lines stay grammatical without collapsing into one stock response.
CHANGELOG.md:171:- Tightened repertoire hook language and payoff shaping: answer-mode hooks now use phrase-level transforms instead of awkward generic suffixes, repertoire memory can target a preferred payoff scene, and tracker runtime state now exposes scene metadata like `payoff_focus` for live correlation.
CHANGELOG.md:184:- Added a motif-driven score generator to `generative_scores.py` and threaded `song_num`, tracker family, cadence state, and recent melodic-memory fragments into live score generation, so CypherClaw can now both invent fresh melody cells and recall transformed motifs instead of rebuilding the same contour-only phrase and comping pattern across similar songs.
