my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:14:2. **Hierarchical arcs.** Section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level arcs, which modulate note-level accents. Arcs compose multiplicatively.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:15:3. **Legible intent.** Every phrase declares an intent tag (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate). Parameters are chosen so the intent is perceptible.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:19:The goal is not realism. It is **legibility**: a listener should feel that CypherClaw *intended* each phrase — to build, to withhold, to answer the room.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:57:  - `render/rules/` — one module per R-rule (metric_accent.py, phrase_arch.py, agogic.py, duration_contrast.py, final_rit.py, punctuation.py, articulation.py, microtiming.py, motif_memory.py, silence_budget.py, call_response.py, sensor_intent.py)
